programme.title: Surfers' Blood
programme.desc: Renowned surf photographer and filmmaker Patrick Trefz explores the essence of the sport he loves by profiling those who inspire him. Surfers' Blood tells the universal story of true individuals that share deep bloodlines connected to the sea. From wooden fishing boats in the Basque Country coast with oar and surfboard shaper Patxi Oliden to the metropolis of San Francisco and the eccentric computer shapes of Apple fame designer Thomas Meyerhoffer, unique people unite by a deep connection to the sea. Watch it on Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Discovering Karpathos
programme.desc: Situated in the Dodecanese Islands and nestled between the coasts of Turkey and Greece we can find Karpathos Island. A paradisiac refuge from sea storms, the island has seen numerous cultures settling along its land. Home to dream-like beaches, quaint towns and impressive natural settings, Karpathos is offers visitors with a relaxed environment that is hard to forget.The island not only has stunning white sand beaches, but the interior offers many riches to those who stop by this destination.Discover Karpathos with us as we venture inside the marvels the island has to offer, accompanied by locals who will be our guides in this resounding adventure.

programme.title: Facing Waves
programme.desc: Facing Waves is an exciting and inspiring TV series that follows top paddlers as they discover the cultures, landscapes and adventures of the world's most amazing adventure travel destinations.Showing spectacular paddling by top athletes in the most stunning locations around the globe, Facing Waves goes from the Dominican Republic to a small town in Wales, facing different conditions in every location, immersing in an unforgettable experience. Adjusting to the customs of locals, challenging huge tidal rapids, kayaking with whales, practicing stand up paddle in the tropics or exploring remote canoe trails in the heart of the jungle are some of the adventures you will see in this show.Facing Waves hosts Ken Whiting, former World Champion Whitewater Kayaker in the trip of his life. Get ready to join their journey with Nautical Channel.

programme.title: Who is J.O.B
programme.desc: Jamie has been living at Pipeline since he was four/five years old. He believes this place he grew up in shaped him into becoming a surfer, and he loves surfing and learning new tricks. He is not the type of guy that tries to hand out with the best surfers in the world. He is who he is and he's ready to show us where he lives, where he surfs and who his friends are.

programme.title: Who is J.O.B
programme.desc: In this second episode of Who is J.O.B Jamie throws down an epic free surf session at Pipeline, where he works on his board transfers. Then, he meets up with Alvert, a North Shore local who resides at the iconic surf spot and is considered by many as eccentric.

programme.title: Iballa Corazón de Escamas
programme.desc: After more than two decades in the world class of sports and overcoming different personal and sporting challenges of great significance, Iballa Ruano Moreno achieved in 2018 an historical landmark unprecedented in professional sports: winning the world championships in the same year the PWA World Circuit of Windsurf and the APP World Tour of Stand Up Paddle. This milestone never before achieved by an active athlete, highlights the level of dedication and improvement that the Moreno Twins and specifically Iballa Ruano, have been successfully reaping for so many years. However, the journey wasn't easy. Corazón de Escamas is a short biographical documentary told in the first person and that shows the most intimate part of its history and is dedicated with great affection to the Ruano Moreno family.

programme.title: Sailing Documentary Show
programme.desc: With unprecedented technological advancements, and a new hydro-foiling GC32 catamaran, the Extreme Sailing Series has done it again! By combining the top class sailing teams and the advanced technological innovations, watching the races has become a pure thrill. With circuits that range through 8 global events, the Extreme Sailing Series is breaking boundaries; both for its sailors and its viewers.

programme.title: Boat Show 4K
programme.desc: We are in Lavezzi, a small island between Corsica and Sardinia. Waters are beautiful, but they are hard to navigate when the wind blows. This is why special vehicles like the Phantom 500 are needed. Besides checking this magnificient boat, we will test drive the SPX RIB 24 and a boat that is the concentration of adrenaline and enjoyment: the Volvo Penta D4 Intervista Svezia Vasterang.

programme.title: Boat Show 4K
programme.desc: We are in Rhode Island to discover the Zeelander Z 72, a beautiful yacht built in the Netherlands but with a strong american heritage. Then, we head on to try the Ferretti Super Yachts Yard Ancona and the Volvo Penta D4 Principe, the boat by choice of an italian gondolier that decided to go for motorboats.

programme.title: Chef on Board
programme.desc: Lapo is back on land for the Surf and Turf Season finale. He will be meeting the Tuscan Cowboys to learn about Tuscany's beef industry as well as taking to the waters with a local fisherman to fish for sea urchins. On this final episode, Lapo is ready to give his all and prove himself worthy of his captain's approval. Will the Captain finally soften to Lapo?
